<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-21T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-21T05:00:00-05:00" n="757" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">467.11/726: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-21T12:00:00+02:00">November 21,
                                        1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>46. From Shaw. “Secretary General Ministry of Foreign Affairs tells
                                me informally that at meetings to take place at Angora in a few days
                                Turks will propose lump sum claims settlement of $500,000. In answer
                                to my question he said that he thought there were only one or two
                                small Turkish claims against the United States.”</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>